Hey there, ru5tyshark here. Thanks for checking out this theme by Tumi, converted by me.
Tumi is the original author of this windows cursor theme and mnay others, which I will be converting and publishing for all to use in the future.
I've tried many times to contact him/her but to no avail, back when I was using windows (I switched to the light side after xp) his/her cursor sets were all I would ever use.
No anit-aliasing or fancy tricks, just straight pixels!
Cursors were originally 32x32 so I've kep inline with this.

To all those using his/her work in your sets (or complete themes!), you should really give credit where it's due. Just saying...

The previews aren't 100% accurate due to gifs being gifs but give a pretty good idea of what to expect.

Install:
Drop 'Tumi's-3D-Crystal' folder into your:
/home/<your-username>/.icons
folder which is usually hidden (depending on your personal settings), so show hidden files/folders in your file manager settings to access it.
Otherwise you will have to sudo copy 'Tumi's-3D-Crystal' folder to /usr/share/icons.
Then goto your cursor theme settings page and select & apply to use.
I've flipped the hand/link cursor as an alternate choice inside the cursors folder if you like.
Enjoy ('-' )
